   </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000">Strategy</Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">This deck basically wins by owerpowering the opponent through Kolte&#39;s Parting Shot. <br>
If you can manage to have a Gia&#39;s Tome in play while you still have Kolte, youll win 90% of the time.  Basically, you should have the following cards in play to achieve almost certain victory:<br>
<br>
Quallon( To weave the 2 you get from the Tuk Berries)<br>
Tuk Berries (Add Energey to Speag/Uwamar)<br>
Gia&#39;s Tome (To recycle the creatures that sacrificed themselves in order to take out a larger one)<br>
Speag/Uwamar, preferrably Speag (To have a large roadblock and/or enegry storage. Beware of Shockwaves)<br>
Any creature to Sacrifice, i found out that Bungaloo works quite well (To attack the opponent with.)<br>
<br>
Ok, once you have those cards in play, heres what you should usually do.  Play the small sacrifice goat (Bungaloo), add as much enegry as needed on to him. Send him to attack a creature that is a few enegry above himself. The parting shot will take out the defender most of the time, and if the Bungaloo and the defender kill themselves mutually, so be it. Bungallo will be back with the tome.  Save all Junjertrugs, Grass and/or Weave Hyren until you have Gia in play. Then Unearth the warriors boots and attack with the 9 or more energy Jungertrug instanlty. That is the way i usually finish off the opponent. If Bo&#39;asha is uncovered, simply defend your speag and/or Zassyfer by all means and you should be fine. The Quallon will be the energy conveyor belt in that situation then. Simply take the 2 energy the Speag gained in the attack and attach them to somebody else as you see fit. <br>
<br>
Now I will explain the spells in the deck.<br>
<br>
Sawgrass: Pretty self explanatory, knock out a treat that attacked last turn. Works quite well with Zaya&#39;s Bow. (Add those if you feel the need)<br>
<br>
The Hunt: Play this before using the Boots to haste the Junjertrug for maximum effect.<br>
<br>
Beam of Light: Take out relics and/or annoying stuff like Flutter Yup<br>
<br>
The rest of the Cards like Relic Stalkers are self explanatory.<br>
<br>
And one more thing, save those pagajacks until you have all 3 in your hand for lots and lots of free energy.<br>
<br>
<br>
This Deck Concept is pretty hard to explain in writing, and if you have any more questions, feel free to send me a message to clarify all confusions<br>
<br>
<br>
Enjoy </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000"> </Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">DeckTech <BR> For the Players, By the Players  <BR>www.decktech.net </FONT></TD></TR></table> 
